{
  "doc_id": "23482",
  "text": "Formal verification and formal specification altogether are called as formal methods [CITATION_1] . Formal specification [CITATION_2] is a technique for specifying the system on the basis of mathematics and logic. It has various techniques and notations, e.g. algebra, logic, table, graphics and automata. After completing the formal specification, we can apply formal verification techniques to the specification to prove that the system satisfies required properties. There are two main approaches in formal verification: deductive reasoning and algorithmic verification.",
